26/04/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- According to local media reports, talks between Belgrade and Pristina about the return of refugees and displaced persons to Kosovo could take place on 12 May.
A UNMIK source was quoted Monday (25 April) as saying dialogue would aim to ensure the collection of necessary data, marking the initial phase of an organised return action.
Also Monday, the Kosovo government announced that a long-delayed census of the population and property would be conducted in the province next spring.
The project will cost an estimated 8m euros.
(KosovaLive, Tanjug - 25/04/05)
